The concept is cute and Christopher is nice but I was underwhelmed.
Given the perfect 5 star rating with 70+ reviews, I knew Cafe Monarch was a must-do on my list for my Scottsdale trip.
I was thrilled when Christopher told me that he could accommodate our party of 3 on Friday night.
We arrived with our bottle of pinot noir (yay for $10 corkage).
It does make it simple that you don't have to decide what to eat.
The first course was a salad course with a grilled half pear and a huge chunk of cheese.
The cheese was delicious and the pear was so juicy and sweet.
The greens were underdressed and not my favorite.
But maybe I'm not a good judge of salads since I don't eat very many.
The second course didn't come out for another 30 minutes and we were getting a bit antsy.
I know that there's only one chef and we should be more patient but I guess we were just hungry.
The second course consisted of ribs and vegetables.
The ribs were actually very tender and the flavor was quite nice; however, since it was a one-man show, the ribs were only lukewarm by the time the plates got to us.
I'm guessing that the ribs were done prior to the vegetables and the whole process just took too long.
There were sweet potatoes and other vegetables on the plate as sides.
The main criticism I would give regarding the meal (which I noticed in both the salad and the entree courses) is that the various things on the plates do not belong harmoniously.
Each item may taste good individually but their combination seems like an afterthought.
Given the amount of flavor in the ribs, I expected the vegetables to be somewhat flavorful as well.
The dessert was pumpkin cheesecake.
I guess pumpkin is kind of holiday-ish but I just don't think it goes that well with cheesecake.
The cheescake tasted more like a pumpkin pie with cream cheese.
The consistency is not as smooth as you would expect in a cheesecake.
Anyway, the entire meal lasted over 2 hours due to the long gaps between courses.
We enjoyed good conversation over good wine so I had a pretty decent time.
However, the bill ended up being $60 per person with tax and tip and I think I've had much better meals at that price point.

