I headed out to Café Monarch for a friend's birthday last Sunday.
The place is tiny and positively filled with atmosphere.
There are only a handful of tables inside, and Chef Chris is able to give personal attention to each one.
We were a little earlier than most of the rest of the folks, so we had the chance to sit and chat with him before he started cooking.
Seriously?
I'd go back just to hang out with the guy.
