The starter white bean soup was bland and the main meal was very, very spicy.
It took about 3 hours to get through only three courses; it was BYOB unfortunately the owner/chef charged us a corking fee.
We were not able to choose what we wanted for dinner, we only noted any food allergies we may have had and the chef prepared surprise spicy beef dishes.
When making the reservation, the owner/chef/waiter offered to make a special birthday treat and asked my boyfriend what my favorite dessert was.
He told him that  I love cupcakes and Chef said he would make them for us.
