I feel like if you take reservations and you only have a certain number of dishes you serve (uhhh two) you can figure how much of each ingredient you need.
Oh well.
Disappointed, we cut into our steaks and took a bite.
It was disgusting.
The sauce that covered the entire filet tasted like burnt funky badness.
I am not one to complain at restaurants, but this was inedible.
I told the server that it tasted burnt and asked him if that was possible (I didn't want them to make me another of the same dish and it turns out I just don't like the way they prepare it).
He said it was possible and took our plates.
At this point, we decided to ask if we could just pay for our salads and go since we had been there an hour and a half and apparently nothing had gotten better since our last visit.
Our server said they had made replacement steaks and were bringing them out shortly, so we waited.
The new steaks had a totally different sauce on them, a red wine reduction, and were much better...still not nearly the best filet I have had, but good.
The dish was a completely different dish than what had been described to us two hours prior (and our server joked with us about that, which I appreciate).
Here's where things turned around.
Our server, Bailey, offered us a couple of cocktails to make up for all that had gone down, so we accepted with much appreciation and the drinks were good.
Our server kept the mood light, joking that he'd bring the dessert out in a couple hours...ha.
He brought it out fairly quickly and with french press coffee.
It was very good, a rum cake with strawberries and blackberries.
Coffee was good as well.
While eating our dessert I overheard another server explaining to another table that something had gone wrong with the equipment so they had to change the sauce on the filet, he even said it tasted bad.
I was so relieved that it wasn't just me.
Anyway, for the price you do get a lot of food, but it still seems like this place may not totally have its act together (except for our wonderful server, that is), so I think it'll be a long while before I give them another try.

