Cafe Monarch lives up to the hype.
The courtyard is a perfectly romantic setting, the food is divine, the service is solid, and the price is well within reason for the experience you get.
I will be regularly checking the ever evolving menu and coming back as much as I reasonably can.
This is an oasis in the desert, I can't believe I waited so long to try it.

I planned a surprise party last week and it could not have turned out better!
Every other place I called wanted a large deposit and could not accommodate 20+ people.
The owners, Phil and his brother, helped me with arranging for the cake delivery and setting everything up.
The venue was great and the food was even better!
Definitely will be going back.

OK- I'm selfish as I read a lot of reviews before going to places but don't post.
I must share my comments as I have to get the word as you don't know what you're missing out on if you don't go.
I took my wife out for her birthday, wondering if it really lives up to the hype.
Cutting to the chase, this was the best pea cold soup, salad, steak (she has the fish), and desert we have ever had, and we've been to some really nice restaurants.
Sound crazy, but the even the coffee I had after the meal was delicious.
So going back, we started off the whole evening with their own house mixed concoctions, which was really tasty.
The atmosphere is what really caught our attention, as the local owners designed everything piece by piece.
They pay attention to the details, making sure everybody was taken care of and everyone got paid that extra special attention we all crave for in a server.
(I spoke with the owner and learned about the history of this place and how they re-designed this)  The couple next to us was celebrating their anniversary, and everybody who was celebrated something received a present from the restaurant.
I wanted to post some pictures but they came out too dark as we went out to the patio afterwards to have another drink.
Misters cooled us down---felt really good.
Bottom line, if you want some REALLY good food and just good service, this is the place.
Will be back soon.
Thank you SO much for the great experience!

I took my wife here for our 2nd year anniversary.
This is by far the most intimate and romantic restaurant that I've been to with phenomenal food and exceptionally great service.
They have set 4 course meal menus that go for $55 per person that changes every few days.
For two people you are looking at $180-200 with tips and drinks.
Very pricy but for special occasions like this, well worth your money.

My hubby and I went here for our anniversary.
We both had the fillet mignon and it was so wonderful and tender.
The appetizer and dessert were great as well.
We sat on the patio and even though it was close to hundred degrees outside the patio was about 20° cooler with the misters that they had going.
We didn't love the salad and I think it would've been great to have an option for two different kind of salads as well as the two options for the dinner entrée.
Other than that though everything else was perfect.
Highly recommend.

